{"lemma":"حاجّ","slug":"حاجّ","root":"ح.ج.ج","root_slug":"ح-ج-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ج-ج","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حاجّ","root":"حجج","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7122","n9423","n9699","n9427","n9701"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%AC%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pilgrim, especially to Mecca"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a title given to people who have performed the pilgrimage to Mecca"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a title given to people who have performed a pilgrimage to Jerusalem"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"camelthorn, manna tree, Alhagi gen. et spp.","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to argue with (someone)","examples":[{"text":"أَلَمْ تَرَ إِلَى الَّذِي حَاجَّ إِبْرَاهِيمَ فِي رَبِّهِ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of حَاجَة (ḥāja)","tags":["form-of","obsolete","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of the verb حَجَّ (ḥajja, “to go on a pilgrimage”).\n\nBorrowed from Aramaic חָגָּה / ܚܓܐ (ḥāggā, “Alhagi”), from Akkadian 𒂊𒄖𒌋 (egû, “Alhagi”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7122","headword_ar":"حَاجٌّ","root":"Hj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"act. part. n. of 1;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Repairing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"betaking himself, to"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a person or place]. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  And hence, (S, Msb,) A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repairing to Mekkeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the Kaabeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to perform the religious rites and ceremonies of the pilgrimage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the purpose of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eumorap","text_ar":"عُمْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb: [but see 1:]) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pilgrim"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Mekkeh; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who has performed the pilgrimage"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Mekkeh: see what follows:] as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAjijN","text_ar":"حَاجِجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) the original form, sometimes used by poetic license: (S:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huj~aAjN","text_ar":"حُجَّاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HajiyjN","text_ar":"حَجِيجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huj~N","text_ar":"حُجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) or rather the second of these is a quasi-pl. n., a kind of noun which, as well as the coll. gen. n., is often called by the lexicographers a pl., though not so called by the grammarians: (MF:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAj~N","text_ar":"حَاجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used as a pl., syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huj~aAjN","text_ar":"حُجَّاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAmirN","text_ar":"سَامِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sum~aArN","text_ar":"سُمَّارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) it may be considered as a gen. n., and is sometimes a quasi-pl. n., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAmilN","text_ar":"جَامِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAqirN","text_ar":"بَاقِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) as is also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hij~N","text_ar":"حِجٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a company of pilgrims"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Mekkeh; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pilgrims, collectively;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, L;) and likewise ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~N","text_ar":"حَجٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (So in a marginal note in a copy of the S.) The fem. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAj~apN","text_ar":"حَاجَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAj~u","text_ar":"حَوَاجُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAj~u bayoti A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"حَوَاجُّ بَيْتِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"when they have performed the pilgrimage; but when they have not yet performed it, [being in the act of performing it,] you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAj~u bayota A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"حَوَاجُّ بَيْتَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in which latter case you would say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAj~N","text_ar":"حَوَاجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"were not this word imperfectly decl.; [and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAj~u bayoti A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"حَاجُّ بَيْتِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAj~N bayota A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"حَاجٌّ بَيْتَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] like as you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAribu zayodK A^amosi","text_ar":"ضَارِبُ زَيْدٍ اَمْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAribN zayodFA gadFA","text_ar":"ضَارِبٌ زَيْدًا غَدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) [↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAj~iY~N","text_ar":"حَاجِّىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as a n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAj~N","text_ar":"حَاجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", considering the latter as a coll. gen. n., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruwmN","text_ar":"رُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which the n. un. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruwmiY~N","text_ar":"رُومِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is commonly used by the Turks and Persians as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pilgrim"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Mekkeh: but I have not found it so used in any classical Arabic work.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqobala AlHaAj~u waAld~aAj~u","text_ar":"اَقْبَلَ الحَاجُّ وَالدَّاجُّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The company of pilgrims"},{"kind":"text","text":"to Mekkeh,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and of men travelling for mercantile purposes, came."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dj","text_ar":"دج"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA daAj~apF","text_ar":"وَلَا دَاجَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo yatoruko","text_ar":"لَمْ يَتْرُكْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He left not a company of pilgrims"},{"kind":"text","text":"to Mekkeh ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamaAEapF HaAj~apF","text_ar":"جَمَاعَةً حَاجَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor a company of their followers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dependents."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA from a trad. [See also arts."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dj","text_ar":"دج"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dwj","text_ar":"دوج"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Overcoming in"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an argument,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a plea,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","A","MF","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n9423","headword_ar":"حَاجَ","root":"Hwj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHuwju","text_ar":"يَحُوجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawojN","text_ar":"حَوْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtAj","text_ar":"احتاج","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiHotiyaAjN","text_ar":"اِحْتِيَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHowaja","text_ar":"اَحْوَجَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) [the second of which is the most common;] the last, irreg. [for by rule it should be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHaAja","text_ar":"اَحَاجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (MF;) are syn.; (S, Msb, * K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAja","text_ar":"حَاجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHiyju","text_ar":"يَحِيجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayojN","text_ar":"حَيْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies the same; (M, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, wanted, needed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"required."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAj A_ilayohi","text_ar":"حاج اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyh","text_ar":"اليه"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtAj","text_ar":"احتاج","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtAjhu","text_ar":"احتاجهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, wanted, needed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"required, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [And in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ano yafoEala ka*aA","text_ar":"اَنْ يَفْعَلَ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtAj","text_ar":"احتاج","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He wanted, needed, required,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"found it necessary, to do,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that he should do, such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY fulaAnK","text_ar":"اـِلَى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AuHotiyja","text_ar":"اُحْتِيجَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one was wanted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"needed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (JK in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xl","text_ar":"خل"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAj","text_ar":"حاج"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. and inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He desired, sought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sought after."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAj","text_ar":"حاج"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtAj","text_ar":"احتاج","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, poor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in poverty"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"want"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"need."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","M","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n9699","headword_ar":"حَاجَ","root":"Hyj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHiyju","text_ar":"يَحِيجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kr, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayojN","text_ar":"حَيْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAja","text_ar":"حَاجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHuwju","text_ar":"يَحُوجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Kr, K:) extr., because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAjapN","text_ar":"حَاجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is its logical root] is [originally]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Kr","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n9427","headword_ar":"حَاجٌ","root":"Hwj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAjapN","text_ar":"حَاجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain kind of thorny plant"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tree."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) See art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hyj","text_ar":"حيج"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n9701","headword_ar":"حَاجٌ","root":"Hyj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", a coll. gen. n., n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain kind of thorny plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a plant of the sour kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina AlHamoDi","text_ar":"مِنَ الحَمْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): accord. to ISd,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of thorny plant"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tree, i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaburN","text_ar":"كَبُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caper"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain plant different from that just named:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain kind of tree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to AHn,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an evergreen, of which the roots extend far into the ground; which, cooked, is used as a medicine; having slender and long leaves, seeming as numerous as the thorns:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asparago sylvestri similis:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Golius, from Ibn-Beytár:) this name, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAquwl","text_ar":"عَاقُول"},{"kind":"text","text":", are now applied by the Arabs to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plant called by European botanists hedysarum alhagi:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAquwlN","text_ar":"عَاقُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taranojubiynN","text_ar":"تَرَنْجُبِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] dim. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuyayojN","text_ar":"حُيَيْجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; therefore its medial radical letter is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiyayojN","text_ar":"حِيَيْجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a chaste dial. var. of this dim., agreeably with a usage observed in similar cases [when the medial radical letter is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}